==Rivalries==
{{main|Algeria–Tunisia football rivalry|Egypt–Tunisia football rivalry}}

[[File:Tunisia vs Algeria 2013 AFCON.jpg|thumb|Tunisia against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] at the [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations]] in South Africa.]]
Tunisia's main football rivals are its neighbours Algeria, Morocco, and Egypt, with which it shares close cultural and political relations. Tunisia have played 45 games against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]]. After the [[Algerian War|independence of Algeria]], a friendly match took place at the [[Stade Chedly Zouiten]].<ref>{{Cite journal |date=1983 |title= An Approach to "Halokinematics" and Interplate Tectonics (North-Central Algeria)|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1306/bf9ab60a-0eb6-11d7-8643000102c1865d |journal= Journal of Petroleum Geology|volume=6 |doi=10.1306/bf9ab60a-0eb6-11d7-8643000102c1865d |issn=0141-6421|last1= Fakhry A. Assaad|url-access=subscription}}</ref> The teams also met three times in the [[FIFA World Cup qualification|qualifying phase of the World Cup]] in [[1970 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|1970]], [[1978 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|1978]] and [[1986 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|1986]]. The overall record slightly favours the Algerians with 16 wins, 14 draws and 14 losses. Algeria and Tunisia have played three times in official competitions: twice in the [[Africa Cup of Nations]], in [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations|2013]] and [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations|2017]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 December 2019 |title=TUN 1-0 ALG: Tunisia - Algeria |url=https://www.flashscore.com/match/0llPI9un/#match-summary |access-date=16 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211045638/https://www.flashscore.com/match/0llPI9un/#match-summary |archive-date=11 December 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=11 December 2019 |title=ALG 1-2 TUN: Algeria - Tunisia |url=https://www.flashscore.com/match/M5B8KeYT/#match-summary |access-date=16 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211045642/https://www.flashscore.com/match/M5B8KeYT/#match-summary |archive-date=11 December 2019 }}</ref> which Tunisia won both times, and once in the [[FIFA Arab Cup]] in [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup|2021]], which Algeria won.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tunisia v Algeria, 18 December 2021 |url=https://www.11v11.com/matches/tunisia-v-algeria-18-december-2021-373407/ |access-date=16 August 2022 |website=11v11.com}}</ref> Egypt and Tunisia have met 35 times in both official and friendly matches. Tunisia have won 16 matches against Egypt's 11, while 8 matches have ended in a draw.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tunisia national football team: record v Egypt |url=https://www.11v11.com/teams/tunisia/tab/opposingTeams/opposition/Egypt/ |access-date=16 August 2022 |website=www.11v11.com}}</ref> Tunisia and [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] have played 50 games since their independence from France in 1956.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tunisia national football team: record v Morocco |url=https://www.11v11.com/teams/tunisia/tab/opposingTeams/opposition/Morocco/ |access-date=16 August 2022 |website=www.11v11.com}}</ref> Tunisia first played Morocco in [[1962 FIFA World Cup qualification|1962 World Cup qualification]] on 30 October 1960 in [[Casablanca]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco v Tunisia, 30 October 1960 |url=https://www.11v11.com/matches/morocco-v-tunisia-30-october-1960-227773/ |access-date=16 August 2022 |website=11v11.com}}</ref> Many matches were played in [[FIFA World Cup qualification|World Cup qualification]] as they met in [[1962 FIFA World Cup|1962]], [[1970 FIFA World Cup|1970]], [[1978 FIFA World Cup|1978]], [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]], [[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]] and [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]] qualifying.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tunisia v Morocco, 08 October 2005 |url=https://www.11v11.com/matches/tunisia-v-morocco-08-october-2005-255012/ |access-date=16 August 2022 |website=11v11.com}}</ref> They also met four times in the African Cup of Nations. Two of them ended in a draw in [[1978 African Cup of Nations|1978]] and [[2000 African Cup of Nations|2000]] and the other two matches ended up as a Tunisian win in the [[2004 African Cup of Nations|2004]] and [[2012 Africa Cup of Nations|2012]] AFCONs.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco v Tunisia, 23 January 2012 |url=https://www.11v11.com/matches/morocco-v-tunisia-23-january-2012-297047/ |access-date=16 August 2022 |website=11v11.com}}</ref> 

