==Honours==
{{Main|Tunisia national football team honours}}

Throughout its history, according to FIFA statutes the Tunisian national team has won two official senior titles, the [[2004 African Cup of Nations|2004 Africa Cup of Nations]] and the [[2011 African Nations Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=African Nations Cup 2004 |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/04a.html |access-date=2023-06-10 |website=www.rsssf.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=African Nations Championship 2011 |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/2011anch.html |access-date=2023-06-10 |website=www.rsssf.org}}</ref> It also won two regional competitions, the [[1963 Arab Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arab Cup |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tablesa/arabcup.html |access-date=2023-06-10 |website=www.rsssf.org}}</ref> organized by [[Union of Arab Football Associations|UAFA]] and the [[1973 Palestine Cup of Nations]]. The team has also won nine friendly titles, including international friendly tournaments listed below.

{{col-begin|width=100%}}
{{Col-3}}
